-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation of the java version of nodegui.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Requirement:
	JavaTM 2 Platform, Standard Edition (J2SETM) 1.4.1
	http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.1/download.html


Compile:

   Linux:
	javac -classpath ./class/nodeclass.jar:. nodegui.java

   Windows:
	javac -classpath .\class\nodeclass.jar;. nodegui.java

Run:

   Linux:
	java -classpath ./class/nodeclass.jar:. nodegui http://host:port

   Windows:
	java -classpath .\class\nodeclass.jar;. nodegui http://host:port

   If [http://host:port] is not specified, a GUI launcher will appear.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install nodegui as Applet
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Compile:

   Linux:
	javac -classpath ./class/nodeclass.jar:. nodeapplet.java

   Windows:
	javac -classpath .\class\nodeclass.jar;. nodeapplet.java

Edit Policy file:
	[$HOMEJAVA]/jre/lib/security/java.policy
	Add:
		permission java.net.SocketPermission "[Your host]:1024-", "accept, connect, listen";
	
	This allows anyone to accept, connect, listen on [Your host] from any ports > 1023.


Run:
	appletviewer nodeapplet.html

If you run the applet via a webserver, edit the file nodeapplet.html and update the java code path:

	
	-Line 22:	document.writeln('java_codebase="http://stratocaster.scripps.edu/xmlrpc/applet/"');
	-Line 31:	<PARAM NAME="java_codebase" VALUE="http://stratocaster.scripps.edu/xmlrpc/applet/">


